07/03/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Crin Antonescu was re-elected as the leader of National Liberal Party (PNL) at a party congress on Saturday (March 6th). He secured 986 of the votes, while his rival Ludovic Orban was backed by 357 delegates. The congress also voted the entire leadership proposed by Antonescu in choosing the party's vice-presidents and others top positions. Antonescu ran as the PNL candidate in the 2009 presidential elections and finished third with 20% of the votes. (Mediafax, Agerpres - 06/03/10)
